Energy futures now set thestandard for oil pricing, said Arnold Safer, president of TheEnergy Futures Group Inc, a consulting firm.     "Petroleum futures trading at the New York MercantileExchange literally set spot market prices in the U.S.," hesaid, adding that some oil products sellers now offer contractsbased on a daily average of NYMEX prices.     He also said that petroleum futures are a major market foroil companies as well as for commodity traders. His remarkswere made at the National Petroleum Refiners Association. Reuter&#3;